Assembler Syntax

AE_MULZAAAAQ32X16 aed0..15(opnd_ae_sem_mul_x2_S1_q0), aed0..15(opnd_ae_sem_mul_x2_S1_d0), aed0..15(opnd_ae_sem_mul_x2_S1_v1), aed0..15(opnd_ae_sem_mul_x2_S1_d2)

C Syntax

#include <xtensa/tie/xt_hifi2.h>

extern ae_int64 AE_MULZAAAAQ32X16(ae_int32x2 d0, ae_int32x2 d1, ae_int16x4 d2);

Description

AE_MULZAAAAQ32X16 is a 32x16-bit signed integer quad MAC with 64-bit result without saturation. The initial accumultator contents are zeroed before writing into the accumulator. AAAA indicates that all four multiply results are added into the accumulator.

Implementation Pipeline

In Out
opnd_ae_sem_mul_x2_S1_d0 Mstage, opnd_ae_sem_mul_x2_S1_v1 Mstage, opnd_ae_sem_mul_x2_S1_d2 Mstage opnd_ae_sem_mul_x2_S1_q0 Wstage
